{"insight":"Every truth needs a guard","plainSummary":"A teaching stays alive when its practice protects it from becoming an excuse.","atAGlance":"A bright insight can be stolen by the part of us it was meant to free. Its practice is the guard that keeps it honest. When the guard is missing, humility can become pride, freedom can become evasion, and love can become grasping. To compare teachings well, ask what each one is trying to protect against.","match":["misuse guard"],"tags":["practice","humility","discernment","insight"]}
